The paper deals with interactive information retrieval (IIR) and proposes a method of using term-mouse-fixations to estimate topical user interests. This involves analyzing user behavior in a domain-specific digital library, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of mouse fixations also relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). The paper also mentions the use of titles and keywords from documents, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL). The analysis of user behavior and fixation times can also be seen as a machine learning task (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with user privacy and data protection, which falls under cybersecurity (cs.CY).
